---

## Empty State UI Patterns — Full Findings

### 1. CSS Variables Available (from `client/src/index.css`)

**Light theme (`:root`):**
- Backgrounds: `--bg-primary: #FAF9F6`, `--bg-secondary: #F3F1ED`, `--bg-hover: #EDEAE5`, `--bg-elevated: #FFFFFF`, `--bg-card: #FEFEFE`, `--bg-pill: rgba(120,100,80,0.06)`, `--bg-glass: rgba(255,255,255,0.55)`, `--bg-glass-border: rgba(200,180,150,0.2)`
- Text: `--text-primary: #1A1612`, `--text-heading: #12100D`, `--text-secondary: #6B6560`, `--text-body: #8A8480`, `--text-muted: #A8A29E`, `--text-faint: #C0BBB5`, `--text-separator: #D9D4CE`
- Borders: `--border-card: rgba(120,100,80,0.08)`, `--border-light: rgba(120,100,80,0.12)`
- Accents: `--accent-amber: #D4A853`, `--accent-sage: #8A9E7A`, `--accent-purple: #C4943E`
- Shadows: `--shadow-card`, `--shadow-modal`, `--shadow-dropdown`
- Fonts: `--font-ui: "Outfit"`, `--font-serif: "Lora"`; also "Lexend Deca" used for headings/numbers

**Dark theme (`[data-theme="dark"]`):**
- Backgrounds: `--bg-primary: #0C0C0C`, `--bg-card: #161614`, `--bg-elevated: #1A1A18`, `--bg-glass: rgba(255,255,255,0.05)`, `--bg-glass-border: rgba(255,240,210,0.08)`
- Text faint becomes `#504A45`, muted `#6B6560`, secondary `#B0A89E`
- Accents shift: `--accent-amber: #E0BA6A`, `--accent-sage: #9AB08A`

---

### 2. The Primary Empty State Pattern — `collection.css` + Collections components

**File:** `client/src/components/collections/collection.css` (lines 1000–1046)

This is the most complete, polished empty state pattern in the codebase:

```css
/* ── Empty state ── */
.no-collections-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 200px;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 14px;
}
.empty-state-icon-ring {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 52px;
    height: 52px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--bg-glass);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--bg-glass-border);
    color: var(--text-faint);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}
.empty-state-icon {
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    color: var(--text-faint);
}
.empty-state-title {
    font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}
.empty-state-description {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 240px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
}
```

**Usage pattern in JSX** (two variants):

**Variant A — icon-ring with SVG + title + description** (`CollectionViewer.jsx`, `ViewUserCollections.jsx`):
```jsx
<div className="no-collections-container">
    <div className="empty-state-icon-ring">
        <svg xmlns="..." height="28px" width="28px" fill="currentColor">...</svg>
    </div>
    <h3 className="empty-state-title">No collections yet</h3>
    <p className="empty-state-description">This user hasn't created any collections.</p>
</div>
```

**Variant B — large standalone icon + title + description + CTA button** (`CollectionJournalCards.jsx`):
```jsx
<div className="no-collections-container">
    <svg className="empty-state-icon" xmlns="..." viewBox="0 0 24 24"
         fill="none" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="1.5"
         strokeLinecap="round" strokeLinejoin="round">
        ...
    </svg>
    <h3 className="empty-state-title">No journals yet</h3>
    <p className="empty-state-description">Start building your collection by adding journals you've written.</p>
    <div className="btn-collection btn-collection--primary">Add your first journal</div>
</div>
```

---

### 3. Inline / Minimal Empty States — `search-empty-state`

**File:** `client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/postcards.css` (lines 186–212)

Used throughout PostCards, ExplorePage, and UserSearchResults — the most frequently reused pattern:

```css
.search-empty-state {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 2rem 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.01rem;
}
.search-empty-state.is-canvas-only {
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.28rem;
}
.search-empty-link {
    border: none;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--accent-sage);
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    font-weight: 650;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: underline;
}
```

Usage examples:
- `"No matching people found."` — `UserSearchResults.jsx`
- `"No matching posts found."` — `PostCards.jsx`, `ExplorePage.jsx`
- `"No posts available right now."` — `ExplorePage.jsx`
- `"Search failed. Please try again."` — multiple places

---

### 4. Following Feed Empty State — Inline styles (PostCards.jsx line 731)

An ad-hoc inline-styled variant (not a named class):

```jsx
<div className="following-empty-state"
     style={{ textAlign: 'center', padding: '3rem 1rem', color: 'var(--text-secondary)' }}>
    <p>Your Following feed is empty</p>
    <p style={{ fontSize: '0.85rem', marginTop: '0.5rem' }}>Follow writers to see their posts here</p>
</div>
```
This is a less refined, one-off pattern using inline styles — no corresponding CSS class defined.

---

### 5. Gallery Empty State — `gallery.css` (line 79)

```css
.gallery-empty-state {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 50vh;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--text-faint);
}
```

Usage: `<div className="gallery-empty-state">No public canvases yet.</div>` — very minimal, just centered text in a tall container.

---

### 6. Profile Media Empty State — `myprofile.css` (line 1071)

```css
.profile-media-empty-state {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1rem 0.25rem 0.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    opacity: 0.75;
}
```

Usage: plain `<p className="profile-media-empty-state">No media found in your buckets yet.</p>` — very minimal inline paragraph.

---

### 7. StoryDashboard Empty State — `StoryDashboard.css` (line 64)

```css
.story-dashboard-empty {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 60px 20px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
}
.story-dashboard-empty p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
}
```

Usage:
```jsx
<div className="story-dashboard-empty">
    <p>You haven't written any stories yet.</p>
    <button className="story-dashboard-new-btn" onClick={...}>Write Your First Story</button>
</div>
```
This one uses a CTA button, but no icon. Raw numeric padding (px, not rem).

---

### Summary of Design Language for Empty States

| Pattern | Icon | Title style | Body text | Color | CTA |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Collections (canonical) | 52px glass ring with 28px SVG, OR 64px standalone SVG | "Lexend Deca" 1rem 600 `--text-secondary` | 0.8rem `--text-muted` max-width 240px | `--text-faint` / `--text-muted` | Optional, uses `.btn-collection--primary` |
| `search-empty-state` | None | None (just one line of text) | 0.84rem `--text-faint` centered | `--text-faint` | Optional link in `--accent-sage` underlined |
| Gallery | None | None | 0.86rem `--text-faint` | `--text-faint` | None |
| Following feed | None | Two paragraphs | 0.85rem `--text-secondary` | `--text-secondary` | None |
| Profile media | None | None | 0.85rem, opacity 0.75 | inherited | None |
| StoryDashboard | None | `<p>` 0.95rem | `--text-secondary` | `--text-secondary` | Yes, a button |

**Canonical/best pattern** is the collections one: centered column, `no-collections-container` wrapper with `2.5rem 1.5rem` padding, glass-ring icon, Lexend Deca title in `--text-secondary`, description in `--text-muted` at 0.8rem, max-width 240px, with optional CTA button. For inline/lightweight empty states, `search-empty-state` (centered, `--text-faint`, `var(--font-ui)`, 0.84rem, 2rem vertical padding) is the standard.

